    {
      "id": "save-refresh-reader",
      "type": "port",
      "label": "Save, Refresh, And Trust Reader",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 960,
        "y": -1935
      },
      "width": 320,
      "height": 210,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-interface-save-refresh-trust"
        },
        "view": {
          "intent": "node",
          "payload": "node.web.detail"
        },
        "renderShape": {
          "kind": "markdown"
        },
        "markdown": "# Save, Refresh, And Trust\n---\n\nThis lesson explains how to tell where your graph lives, what a save actually commits, what refresh or reopen should reload, and how to recover confidence when the app state feels suspicious."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "save-refresh-intro",
      "type": "tutorial-title",
      "label": "Lesson Hero",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 1410,
        "y": -1935
      },
      "width": 620,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Save, Refresh, And Trust",
        "subtitle": "Learn how save targets, refresh, reopen, and GitHub-backed state are supposed to behave so you can tell whether your graph is actually safe, current, and trustworthy.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "tutorial-title",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-title.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-title.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "tutorial-title",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-title.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "tutorial-title",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-interface-save-refresh-trust"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "save-refresh-target-note",
      "type": "tutorial-concept",
      "label": "Save Target",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 2180,
        "y": -2215
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Know What You Are Saving",
        "body": "Trust starts with the save target. A graph at a GitHub address, a local scratch graph, and a temporary working state are not the same thing, even if the UI looks similar while you edit them.",
        "tag": "Concept",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "tutorial-concept",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-concept.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-concept.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "tutorial-concept",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-concept.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "tutorial-concept",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-interface-save-refresh-trust"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "save-refresh-reload-note",
      "type": "tutorial-concept",
      "label": "Refresh And Reopen",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 2180,
        "y": -1915
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Refresh Reloads State",
        "body": "Refresh and reopen are recovery tools. They help you reread the current source of truth instead of trusting a stale tab, an accidental transient state, or a mental model that no longer matches the graph on disk.",
        "tag": "Concept",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "tutorial-concept",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-concept.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-concept.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "tutorial-concept",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-concept.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "tutorial-concept",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-interface-save-refresh-trust"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "save-refresh-recovery-note",
      "type": "tutorial-concept",
      "label": "Trust And Recovery",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 2180,
        "y": -1615
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Recover Confidence Deliberately",
        "body": "When something feels off, slow down and verify the address, the save target, and whether the current tab reflects persisted data. Trust comes from deliberate checks, not from hoping the last click did what you meant.",
        "tag": "Concept",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "tutorial-concept",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-concept.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-concept.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "tutorial-concept",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-concept.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "tutorial-concept",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-interface-save-refresh-trust"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "save-refresh-example",
      "type": "tutorial-example",
      "label": "Examples",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 2740,
        "y": -1915
      },
      "width": 400,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Examples",
        "body": "Use the checklist below when you are unsure whether a graph change is really persisted and whether a reload should keep or discard what you are seeing.",
        "cta": "Inspect the checklist",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "tutorial-example",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-example.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-example.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "tutorial-example",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-example.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "tutorial-example",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-interface-save-refresh-trust"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "save-refresh-checklist",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Trust Checklist",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 3310,
        "y": -2060
      },
      "width": 430,
      "height": 340,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-interface-save-refresh-trust"
        },
        "markdown": "## Trust checklist\n\n1. What address am I on right now?\n2. Is this graph local, provisional, or GitHub-backed?\n3. Did I save before I refreshed?\n4. If I reopen this graph, what source of truth should reload?\n5. If something looks wrong, should I refresh, reopen, or navigate back to a known-good graph?\n6. Can I explain why I trust the current state?\n\nIf you cannot answer those questions, slow down before you keep editing."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "save-refresh-challenge",
      "type": "tutorial-challenge",
      "label": "Challenge",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 3310,
        "y": -1670
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Challenge",
        "body": "1. Make one visible change in a graph.\n2. State where that graph is saved.\n3. Save it deliberately.\n4. Refresh or reopen the graph.\n5. Explain why the result matches, or fails to match, your expectations.",
        "difficulty": "starter",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "tutorial-challenge",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-challenge.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-challenge.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "tutorial-challenge",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-challenge.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "tutorial-challenge",
